   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Part 1: Ollama"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "ae9a930c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "What is Ollama?\n",
    "Ollama is a wrapper service around llama.cpp (and other inference engines).\n",
    "- A user-friendly API server\n",
    "- Model management system (pull, list, delete)\n",
    "- Built-in modelfile format for configuration\n",
    "- REST API that's OpenAI-compatible\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Pros: Easy setup, great for beginners, model library\n",
    "Cons: Additional overhead, less control over inference parameters"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "68f80ab6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Part 2: Hardware Understanding"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "fca48a20",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "- 10 CPU cores (6 performance + 4 efficiency)\n",
    "- 16GB+ unified memory (shared between CPU/GPU)\n",
    "- Metal GPU with 16-core neural engine\n",
    "Key Insight: On Apple Silicon, the GPU shares memory with the CPU (unified memory architecture). This means:\n",
    "- No data transfer overhead between CPU ↔ GPU\n",
    "- GPU can access all system RAM\n",
    "- Metal Performance Shaders (MPS) accelerate matrix operations\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "M1 Pro GPU Reality\n",
    "The M1 Pro has an integrated GPU with 16 cores built into the same chip as the CPU. It's not a separate graphics card like an NVIDIA RTX, but it IS a real GPU that can:\n",
    "- Run Metal shaders (Apple's GPU programming framework)\n",
    "- Accelerate matrix operations (critical for LLMs)\n",
    "- Process multiple sequences in parallel\n",
    "Key difference: It's unified memory architecture:\n",
    "- CPU and GPU share the same RAM\n",
    "- No copying data between CPU memory ↔ GPU memory\n",
    "- The GPU can access all 16GB+ of system RAM"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0f3e09e1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Part 3: Concurrency Problem"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "8dba9aee",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1. Memory-bound: Loading model into VRAM/RAM is expensive\n",
    "2. compute-intensive: Generating tokens uses CPU heavily \n",
    "3. Sequential in nature: Each token depends on previous tokens"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b7246a58",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Concurrency Strategies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "ef50b17d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Strategy 1: Sequential Processing (naive)\n",
    "    \n",
    "Request 1 → Process → Response\n",
    "Request 2 → Process → Response\n",
    "Request 3 → Process → Response\n",
    "- Simple but slow for multiple users\n",
    "- Total time = sum of all request times"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "5e438433",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Strategy 2: True Parallelism\n",
    "\n",
    "Request 1 ↘\n",
    "Request 2 → [LLM Engine] → All responses simultaneously\n",
    "Request 3 ↗\n",
    "- Requires inference engine support\n",
    "- Limited by GPU memory and compute units\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "88dc3153",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Strategy 3: Batching\n",
    "\n",
    "Batch 1: [Req1, Req2, Req3, Req4] → Process together\n",
    "Batch 2: [Req5, Req6, Req7, Req8] → Process together\n",
    "- Group requests together\n",
    "- Process multiple in one forward pass\n",
    "- More efficient GPU utilization"
   ]
  },
  {
